### TITLE ###
MissingColonAfterIfFiresRAD10002
### DESCRIPTION ###
A block-opening keyword without its trailing colon fires
RAD10002 (Missing Colon) with a specific message and an
actionable suggestion. Previously this shape produced the
generic RAD10009 "Unexpected token".
### INPUT ###
if x
    y = 5
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  (none)

# Symbol types
  (none)

# Diagnostics
  [error] RAD10002 @ 1:1 - Missing ':' after 'if' header
    help: add ':' at the end of the line
### TITLE ###
MissingColonAfterForFiresRAD10002
### DESCRIPTION ###
The detector recognises the same shape across every block-
opening keyword (if/elif/else/for/while/fn/switch/case/defer).
### INPUT ###
for i in [1, 2, 3]
    print(i)
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  (none)

# Symbol types
  (none)

# Diagnostics
  [error] RAD10002 @ 1:1 - Missing ':' after 'for' header
    help: add ':' at the end of the line
  [error] RAD10009 @ 1:10 - Unexpected '[1, 2, 3]'
### TITLE ###
MissingIndentAfterIfFiresRAD10018
### DESCRIPTION ###
A header with a colon but no indented body fires RAD10018
(Missing Indent). Tree-sitter doesn't emit a MISSING "indent"
node for this shape, so we recognise it from the ERROR
content directly.
### INPUT ###
if true:
y = 5
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  (none)

# Symbol types
  (none)

# Diagnostics
  [error] RAD10018 @ 1:1 - Missing indent after 'if:' block header
    help: indent the body of the block
### TITLE ###
UnterminatedStringFiresRAD10020
### DESCRIPTION ###
An opening quote with no matching close on the same line
fires RAD10020 (Unterminated String). The detector handles
the case where tree-sitter records the open quote as a
one-char ERROR token by scanning forward in the source.
### INPUT ###
a = "hello
b = 5
### STDOUT ###
# Identifier types
  a @ 1:1 -> <no-type>
  hello @ 1:6 -> dynamic
  b @ 2:1 -> <no-type>

# Symbol types
  a (local): dynamic
  b (local): int

# Diagnostics
  [error] RAD10020 @ 1:5 - Unterminated string literal (missing closing double quote)
    help: add closing " before end of line
